# agent-relay — environment variables (all optional).
#
# Core reads these directly from the PROCESS environment — it does NOT auto-load a
# .env file. Export the ones you want before launching Copilot, e.g.:
#     $env:AGENT_RELAY_NAME = "alice"   # PowerShell
#     export AGENT_RELAY_NAME=alice     # bash / zsh
# (This file is a reference; copying it to .env has no effect on core. Cross-machine /
# Postgres settings live with the agent-relay-pg-plugin, not here.)

# Address this session in the mesh (default: a deterministic word alias from the session id).
# AGENT_RELAY_NAME=alice

# Directory for local state (the SQLite store) + rolling diagnostic logs. Defaults
# to a per-user OS data dir (e.g. %LOCALAPPDATA%\agent-relay on Windows,
# ~/Library/Application Support/agent-relay on macOS, $XDG_DATA_HOME/agent-relay (or
# ~/.local/share/agent-relay) on Linux). Override to relocate them.
# AGENT_RELAY_DATA_DIR=C:\path\to\agent-relay-data

# Use a specific SQLite file for the local store (overrides the data-dir default).
# AGENT_RELAY_DB=C:\path\to\agent-relay.db

# Load EXTERNAL plugin modules (interceptors / transport / credentials / identity) at
# startup, folded into a registry — so a capability can live in a separate (private) repo
# or a local folder, not in this one. Both optional; with no paths set AND no plugins in
# the plugin dir, nothing loads. Each module default-exports a factory (ctx)=>Registration —
# see the README "External plugins" section for the contract.
#   - AGENT_RELAY_PLUGINS:    comma-separated module paths (absolute or cwd-relative),
#     loaded in listed order (a secondary dev convenience).
#   - AGENT_RELAY_PLUGIN_DIR: a folder whose top-level *.mjs + package subfolders are loaded
#     alphabetically (default: the extension's OWN plugins/ folder, next to extension.mjs).
# AGENT_RELAY_PLUGINS=C:\path\to\my-plugin\index.mjs
# AGENT_RELAY_PLUGIN_DIR=C:\path\to\agent-relay-plugins
